<li id="cite_note-25"><b><a href="#cite_ref-25" title="">^</a></b> (Mehmed Fuad Koprulu's , Early Mystics in Turkish Literature, Translated by Gary Leiser and Robert Dankoff , Routledge, 2006, pg 149)</li>
<li id="cite_note-26"><b><a href="#cite_ref-26" title="">^</a></b> M.B. Dickson and S.C. Welch, <i>The Houghton Shahnameh</i> 2 vols (Cambridge Mmssachusetts and London. 1981. See: pg 34 of Volume I)</li>
<li id="cite_note-27"><b><a href="#cite_ref-27" title="">^</a></b> R.M. Savory, <i>Safavids</i>, <a href="/wiki/Encyclopedia_of_Islam" title="Encyclopedia of Islam" class="mw-redirect">Encyclopedia of Islam</a>, 2nd edition</li>
<li id="cite_note-28"><b><a href="#cite_ref-28" title="">^</a></b> See: <a href="http://www.farhangiran.com/pdf/shahkurdarmen.pdf" class="external autonumber" title="http://www.farhangiran.com/pdf/shahkurdarmen.pdf" rel="nofollow">[4]</a> <a href="http://www.azargoshnasp.net/famous/ferdowsi/shahkurdarmen.pdf" class="external autonumber" title="http://www.azargoshnasp.net/famous/ferdowsi/shahkurdarmen.pdf" rel="nofollow">[5]</a></li>
<li id="cite_note-29"><b><a href="#cite_ref-29" title="">^</a></b> Encyclopedia Iranica, "Shahnama Translations in Georgian", Jamshid Sh. Giunshvili</li>
</ol>
</div>
